$ Oracle High Availablity
@ High Availablity

The aim of *High Availablity* is to prevent or at least reduce unplanned downtime of an Oracle database.

{ Causes of down time

  A database might become unavailable because of
    • Site failures
    • Computer failures
    • Storage failures
    • Data corruption
    • Human errors
    • Malice

}

